                                         CAPE TOWN - Two people have been killed and several others injured following a collision in Cape Town. During the early hours of Sunday morning, paramedics were called to an accident reported on the N1 near Durban Road. It's unclear what caused the crash, but rescue officials report finding one overturned vehicle and several more which were severely damaged. ER24’s Werner Vermaak says two people were found dead at the scene, while seven others were treated for various injuries before being taken to hospital. “The exact circumstances surrounding the incident is not yet known. Local authorities who were on scene will conduct an investigation.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter) 